mgroup="row" id="r-1670485569581" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670485569581" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1656408976790" data-id="1656408976790"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569817" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569817"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What Are the Benefits Of Using Weightlifting Gloves?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670506608137" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670506608137"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Gloves Provide Comfort</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764626941" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673764626941" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>For most people, the main purpose of getting workout gloves for lifting weights is to make their exercise more comfortable.</p><p>Most gloves have some form of thick comfort padding that eases pressure on the palms, reducing hand fatigue and prolonging your ability to exercise.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569822" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670485569822"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Gloves Protect Your Palms From Injury</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569821" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569821" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Arguably the most important purpose of wearing weightlifting gloves for men and women is to provide a protective surface between the palm and gripped object, preventing injuries. For example, gripping onto barbells for extended periods of time can form thick patches of skin on your palms, called calluses. Experienced athletes are familiar with them.</p><p>By themselves they’re not concerning, although they can cause discomfort if you ignore them and continue to exercise. However, repeated pressure on already existing calluses can cause blisters to form underneath, which can be problematic. Blisters are sacs of fluid that form in response to pressure on the skin.</p><p>If left unchecked, they can be quite painful and require more serious treatment or even a doctor’s visit. If they pop, they can cause bleeding and expose the skin underneath, potentially causing infections.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672895064923" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1672895064923"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Gloves Provide Wrist Support</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672895061465" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1672895061465" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Many weightlifting gloves also provide wrist support by using wraps. Wraps keep the wrist tighly in place and reduce the risk of sprains or strains, which can be very beneficial during heavy lifting exercises such as deadlifts and bench presses.</p><p><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-wrist-wraps-for-lifting" class="" target="_blank">Wrist wraps</a> are especially useful for athletes who have weaker joints that are prone to injury, or chronic pain caused by issues such as carpal tunnel.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781715573" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1675781715573" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d6a243e2-af8f-4d34-8ee5-ca504c9c2ce5/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Weightlifting-Gloves-Dumbbelles.jpg" alt="Weightlifting Gloves with dumbbelles" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678792176165" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1678792176165"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Using Gloves Is Hygienic</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678792176799" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678792176799" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Workout equipment is full of dirt and sweat which can accumulate all kinds of germs and bacteria. If you have any form of micro cuts or skin tears, which can occur from gripping onto bar knurling, this can cause infections.</p><p>A report by Men’s Health <a href="https://www.menshealth.com/health/a19518382/gym-germs/" class="" target="_blank">highlighted</a> that dumbbells can carry as much as 300 more germs than a toilet seat. This point is especially important if you’re using a public gym, where equipment sharing is common.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764710691" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673764710691"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">When Do You Need Weightlifting Gloves?</span></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764700638" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673764700638" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Using weightlifting gloves can be a great way to improve your grip, protect your hands, and provide additional support during weightlifting workouts. The textured surface on the palms of weightlifting gloves helps you have a better grip on the barbell or dumbbell, reducing the risk of the weight slipping out of your hands and causing injury or damaging equipment.</p><p>The palms and fingers of weightlifting gloves feature comfort padding that reduces friction and absorbs shock from heavy lifting, which reduces the likelihood of blisters, calluses, and other hand injuries from occurring. Many weightlifting gloves also provide necessary wrist support by using tightly fitting straps that keep the joint in place, lowering the chance of sprains and reducing overall wrist strain.</p><p>It's important to choose a pair of weightlifting gloves that fit properly and provide the necessary amount of padding and support for your hand shape and size. Gloves that are too loose or too tight can be uncomfortable and won’t provide adequate protection or support. Studies have shown that <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0003687018303739" class="" target="_blank">ill-fitting gloves can result</a> in loss of performance in the hands, which makes exercising harder and increases the risk of dropping equipment, which can cause injuries or damage to your surroundings.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678792322363" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1678792322363" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/7f4ba3ff-2d6f-4e82-aa37-0c71bd2ec8b4/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Weight-lifting-gloves-with-wrist-support.jpg" alt="Gloves for lifting with wirst straps" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="786" height="524" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="786" natural-height="524"></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678792316572" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678792316572" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Using gloves also provides hygienic benefits by serving as a protective barrier for your skin. This is especially important if you use public gyms where equipment is shared between lots of people. Remember to wash your hand gloves regularly to remove sweat stains and prevent the growth of bacteria and other microorganisms. Investing in a pair of high-quality weightlifting gloves can improve your workout experience regardless of your athletic level.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670506766447" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670506766447"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What to Look For in the Best Weightlifting Gloves?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675081935903" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675081935903"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Design</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675081937983" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675081937983" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>While visual design is subjective and mostly comes down to the number of color choices, functional design choices are very important.</p><p>I like products where it’s obvious the manufacturer made a conscious functional design choice based on different athletes’ experiences.</p><p>For example, the Original Mechanix gloves seamless design protects the stitching from regular wear and tear, which prolongs their lifecycle, meaning you get more value for the money spent.</p><p>Unique design choices that set the product apart always get extra points, such as the ATERCEL towel panel, Bear Grips touch screen fingertips, etc.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701368227495" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701368227495" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701368227528" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701368227528" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701368227517" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701368227517"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701368227444" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1701368227444" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="512" natural-height="512"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701368227551" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701368227551"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">Wearing gloves for weightlifting can increase workout comfort and significantly reduce hand fatigue, improving your grip. Exercise gloves also prevent common skin injuries that occur from tight gripping, most notably calluses.</div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701368227505" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701368227505" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564763470" data-id="1686564763470"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701368227521" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1701368227521" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" target="_blank"><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/fc0a1a19-2e31-4fa8-a43b-9c408a123923/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Oleksiy.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="531" height="533" data-width="20%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="531" natural-height="533"></a></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564765807" data-id="1686564765807"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701368227507" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701368227507"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" class="" target="_blank">Oleksiy Torokhtiy</a></b></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701368227579" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701368227579"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700;">Olympic Weightlifting&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781843365" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675781843365"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Comfort</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678792415854" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678792415854"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The phrase “fit like a glove” exists for a reason. Gloves for weight training must be comfortable and fit snugly around the hand, otherwise, they can end up feeling inconvenient and hindering your performance. The main use of training gloves is to create a comfortable protective surface for gripping with your palms.</p><p><br></p><p>Gripping with exposed skin can cause cuts, calluses, blisters, and other skin damage, especially if the gripped surface has a patterned texture such as knurling. Different brands experiment with various comfort features such as breathable mesh, stretching materials, air vents, soft pads of various shapes and sizes, etc. There is not a single ideal solution and the best choice for you will depend on your preferences.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787081135" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1675787081135" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/f744c824-7a6b-4ccf-ab45-67fdb072915e/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/WBCM-WF-and-pullup-glove.jpg" alt="WBCM glovs or grips are good also for pull-ups" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781867139" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675781867139"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Stitching</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678109130171" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678109130171"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Stitching on gloves for lifting weights has to withstand pressure, or else the gloves will break easily, forcing you to waste money on infinite numbers of replacements. Some gloves feature a seamless design, such as the Original Mechanix, but most will have at least some stitching exposed.</p><p><br></p><p>Gloves that have extra stitching will get more points, but the placement of the stitching is equally important. Most stitching gives away between the thumb and index finger, which is why many manufacturers reinforce that part with extra layers.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787155402" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787155402"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Durability</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678109190901" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678109190901"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>How durable a pair of gym gloves for men and women will be will depend on the materials used in construction, the quality of the stitching, but also the frequency of use. All gloves on the list proved durable when tested in average workout conditions, so they’re sufficient for most athlete levels.</p><p><br></p><p>That said, more advanced athletes that perform heavy lifting should pay more attention to the durability rating, and consider item specs as well as the pros and cons before making a purchase.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787197818" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787197818"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Protection</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678109227306" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678109227306"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Lifting gloves serve to provide a safety layer between the palms and the barbell or dumbbell. The protective layer itself already makes exercises safer by preventing cuts and scratches.</p><p><br></p><p>Protective padding is there primarily for comfort, but it also lowers the pressure and friction on the palms. This reduces the risk of calluses, blisters, and other potential skin injuries. Some gloves have extra wrist support using a tight strap.</p><p><br></p><p>These straps can prevent injuries such as sprains or strains that occur during heavy lifting, however, they can also restrict hand movement for some exercises.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787795887" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1675787795887" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/ee523e14-4405-4925-9112-5a0aa4e5bfb9/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Weightlifting-Gloves-Bench-Lifting.jpg" alt="Weightlifting Gloves Bench Lifting" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678792578417" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678792578417"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Price/Quality</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678792579021" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678792579021"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The products with the most value for money usually sit at the top of the list. That said, both budget picks and premium lifting gloves can have a high price/quality rating if they outperform products in a similar price range.</p><p><br></p><p>Getting a poor-quality pair of lifting gloves can be frustrating, as having to buy replacements can rack up the cost over time. My advice would be not to try to save on cost, as the price differences between these products are minimal.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787440275" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787440275"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQ</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787464047" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787464047"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Is It Better to Wear Gloves When Lifting Weights?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678109356404" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678109356404"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>As discussed throughout the article, wearing gloves when lifting has various benefits and almost no drawbacks. Gloves create a protective surface between your hands and the equipment, which prevents common palm injuries, such as cuts, calluses, and blisters.</p><p><br></p><p>Most gloves also have comfort features such as padding and grip texture, that reduce grip fatigue and make your lifting more enjoyable.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787889767" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787889767"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Are Lifting Gloves Better Than Straps?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678109396634" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678109396634"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Lifting gloves and lifting straps serve the same purpose, and both have their benefits. The choice will mostly come down to personal preference. Gloves have many comfort and safety features that protect the palms, which the average athlete will find helpful.</p><p><br></p><p>On the other hand, straps provide a more natural feel that may be preferred by highly advanced athletes whose hands are used to lifting.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787928690" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787928690"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Do Lifting Gloves Weaken Grip?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678109395905" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678109395905"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>If the gloves fit correctly, you won’t notice a difference in grip strength in most exercises, especially weight lifting.</p><p><br></p><p>In fact, studies have shown that exercising with gloves can <a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1518/107118188786762603" class="" target="_blank">increase maximal grip</a> at the cost of a negligible amount of muscle force.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1675788016791" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1675788016791" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module